# Wound Care - Bandages

ent-MedicalItemBandageMakeshift = makeshift bandage
    .desc = A makeshift bandage fashioned from a torn piece of cloth. Not sterile, but better than nothing.

ent-MedicalItemBandageBoiled = boiled bandage
    .desc = A cloth bandage that has been boiled for sterilization. More effective than a raw makeshift bandage.

ent-MedicalItemBandageMedicalGauze = medical gauze
    .desc = Sterile medical gauze for wound dressing. Effective at controlling bleeding from cuts and punctures.

ent-MedicalItemBandageProper = bandage
    .desc = A proper adhesive bandage with antiseptic padding. Standard medical supply.

ent-MedicalItemHemostaticPowder = hemostatic powder
    .desc = A packet of hemostatic granules designed to rapidly control bleeding. Stings on application.

# Wound Care - Antiseptics

ent-MedicalItemAntiseptic = antiseptic
    .desc = Isopropyl alcohol solution for cleaning and disinfecting wounds. Prevents infection.

ent-MedicalItemAntisepticMakeshift = makeshift antiseptic
    .desc = An improvised antiseptic made from ethanol. Less effective than proper disinfectant, but serviceable.

ent-MedicalItemAntisepticPowder = antiseptic powder
    .desc = Bismuth formic iodide in powder form. An effective chemical wound cleanser.

# Pharmaceuticals - Pills

ent-MedicalItemPillAspirin = aspirin
    .desc = Medication to reduce pain, inflammation, and fever.

ent-MedicalItemPillCanisterAspirin = pill canister
    .desc = A bottle of aspirin tablets.

ent-MedicalItemPillIbuprofen = ibuprofen
    .desc = A non-steroidal anti-inflammatory for moderate pain relief.

ent-MedicalItemPillCanisterIbuprofen = pill canister
    .desc = A bottle of ibuprofen tablets.

ent-MedicalItemPillAcetaminophen = acetaminophen
    .desc = A mild over-the-counter painkiller. Effective for minor aches.

ent-MedicalItemPillCanisterAcetaminophen = pill canister
    .desc = A bottle of acetaminophen tablets.

ent-MedicalItemPillCodeine = codeine
    .desc = A mild opiate analgesic for moderate to severe pain.

ent-MedicalItemPillCanisterCodeine = pill canister
    .desc = A bottle of codeine tablets.

ent-MedicalItemPillAntibiotics = antibiotics
    .desc = A broad-spectrum antibacterial medication designed to prevent or stop the spread of infection.

ent-MedicalItemPillCanisterAntibiotics = pill canister
    .desc = A bottle of antibiotic capsules.

ent-MedicalItemPillAntihistamine = antihistamine
    .desc = An antihistamine tablet for allergy relief. May cause drowsiness.

ent-MedicalItemPillCanisterAntihistamine = pill canister
    .desc = A bottle of antihistamine tablets.

ent-MedicalItemPillIodine = potassium iodide
    .desc = Potassium iodide tablet. Saturates the thyroid to prevent radioactive iodine uptake.

ent-MedicalItemPillCanisterIodine = pill canister
    .desc = A bottle of potassium iodide tablets.

ent-MedicalItemPillPrussianBlue = prussian blue
    .desc = A chelating agent that binds radioactive contaminants for excretion. For post-exposure radiation treatment.

ent-MedicalItemPillCanisterPrussianBlue = pill canister
    .desc = A bottle of prussian blue tablets.

ent-MedicalItemPillCharcoal = activated charcoal
    .desc = Activated charcoal capsule. Absorbs toxins and poisons in the gastrointestinal tract.

ent-MedicalItemPillCanisterCharcoal = pill canister
    .desc = A bottle of activated charcoal capsules.

# Injectable Medicine

ent-MedicalItemInjectorEpinephrine = epinephrine autoinjector
    .desc = An emergency epinephrine autoinjector. Stabilizes patients in anaphylactic shock or cardiac arrest.

ent-MedicalItemInjectorMorphine = morphine syrette
    .desc = A military-issue morphine syrette. A strong narcotic painkiller in a squeezable tube with attached needle.

ent-MedicalItemInjectorAntidote = antivenom injector
    .desc = An injectable prophylactic antivenom. Provides broad-spectrum protection against organic toxins.

ent-MedicalItemInjectorStimulant = stimulant injector
    .desc = A military-grade stimulant injector. Increases alertness and reaction time. Side effects include irritability and insomnia.

ent-MedicalItemInjectorRadTreatment = rad treatment injector
    .desc = An emergency radiation treatment injector. For acute radiation exposure. Aggressively chelates radioactive particles.

ent-MedicalItemInjectorCombat = combat trauma pen
    .desc = A combat medical auto-injector loaded with broad-spectrum trauma medication. Designed to get a wounded soldier back in the fight.

ent-MedicalItemInjectorSaline = saline injector
    .desc = A pre-filled saline syringe for fluid resuscitation. Restores blood volume in hemorrhagic shock.

# Herbal & Natural Remedies

ent-MedicalItemHerbalPoppyPainkiller = poppy painkiller
    .desc = A refined opioid analgesic derived from mutant poppies. Effective pain relief with mild sedative properties.

ent-MedicalItemHerbalCattailJelly = cattail jelly
    .desc = A clear protective jelly harvested from cattail stalks. Applied to wounds to prevent contamination and promote healing.

ent-MedicalItemHerbalWintergreenOil = wintergreen oil
    .desc = An oil-based ointment made from wintergreen berries. Has mild antiseptic and analgesic properties.

ent-MedicalItemHerbalThymeOil = thyme oil
    .desc = An aromatic essential oil with natural antiseptic properties. Used topically to treat minor infections.

ent-MedicalItemHerbalMugwortOil = mugwort oil
    .desc = A pungent essential oil derived from mugwort. Traditionally used as an antiparasitic and digestive aid.

ent-MedicalItemHerbalPoppySyrup = poppy cough syrup
    .desc = A thick syrup brewed from mutant poppy pods. Suppresses cough and relieves pain, but may cause drowsiness.

ent-MedicalItemHerbalCharcoalPurified = purified charcoal
    .desc = Hardwood charcoal that has been crushed, washed, and purified. Ingested to absorb toxins and poisons.

# First Aid Kits

ent-MedicalItemKitFirstAid = first aid kit
    .desc = A standard first aid kit containing bandages, painkillers, and antiseptic. Basic but reliable.

ent-MedicalItemKitIFAK = IFAK
    .desc = An Individual First Aid Kit issued to military personnel. Contains supplies for treating combat trauma.

ent-MedicalItemKitHerbalist = herbalist's pouch
    .desc = A leather pouch containing various herbal remedies. Smells of dried herbs and essential oils.

ent-MedicalItemKitTrauma = trauma kit
    .desc = A trauma kit designed for treating catastrophic hemorrhage and severe injuries in the field.
